  <compounddef id="COS" kind="page">
    <compoundname>COS</compoundname>
    <title>COS Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">COS(real-expression)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Returns the <bold>cosine</bold> of the given angle, where the angle is expressed in <bold>radians</bold>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="COS_1autotoc_md482">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>COS(0)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>1</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>COS(PI#<sp/>/<sp/>2)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces approximately <computeroutput>0</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>COS(PI#)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>-1</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Plot<sp/>cosine<sp/>values<sp/>for<sp/>multiples<sp/>of<sp/>45<sp/>degrees</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">FOR<sp/>d<sp/>=<sp/>0<sp/>TO<sp/>360<sp/>STEP<sp/>45</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>r#<sp/>=<sp/>d<sp/>*<sp/>PI#<sp/>/<sp/>180</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;COS(&quot;;<sp/>d;<sp/>&quot;°)<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;;<sp/>COS(r#)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">NEXT</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="COS_1autotoc_md484">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Argument is in <bold>radians</bold>. Convert degrees to radians with:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">radians#<sp/>=<sp/>degrees<sp/>*<sp/>PI#<sp/>/<sp/>180</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Return value is a real number between <computeroutput>-1</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>1</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Related inverse function: <ref refid="ACS" kindref="compound">ACS</ref>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
